<subSubSection id="1554F17377E0063ED103D68A9E00EEBD" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="525F44528F34BC8DDD10DD6F3911B12E" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="502C8A3CC4207D049079F4D8F54FDDDE" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
A member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="DDE705B9CC4CD33FFE128202EA3B144B" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Madascincus</taxonomicName>
based on its molecular phylogenetic relationships (see Fig. 1). Within the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D5978921F4EE41887E3DC9038A1D2490" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Madascincus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C5A1A46BA115E92660182041345828C6" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus pyrurus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyrurus">Madascincus pyrurus</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all its congeners by the following combination of characters: medium body size with a maximum snout-vent length (SVL) of 54.2 mm (versus, in smaller species, a maximum SVL of 33.6 mm in 
<taxonomicName id="E5E694DD75B12DD2E66C859876285F68" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus nanus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">Madascincus nanus</taxonomicName>
complex); 71-79 rows of paravertebral scales (versus 51-62 in 
<taxonomicName id="C95F8D3104497C3D009FB1ABF1194E74" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus melanopleura" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopleura">Madascincus melanopleura</taxonomicName>
, 57-65 in 
<taxonomicName id="AA5FB905FE58B416809DDEC0E1F4F94E" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus minutus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutus">Madascincus minutus</taxonomicName>
, 52-62 in 
<taxonomicName id="882A1ABF12B622A6FE929D17A3FCC026" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus ankodabensis" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ankodabensis">Madascincus ankodabensis</taxonomicName>
, 60-65 in 
<taxonomicName id="3DFF13E59C4F6B4583CDAD53936CED51" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus mouroundavae" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mouroundavae">Madascincus mouroundavae</taxonomicName>
, and 50-57 in 
<taxonomicName id="EF8A821B098F39974591EDFD8B1CF2FA" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus nanus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">Madascincus nanus</taxonomicName>
complex); 73-78 rows of ventral scales (versus 55-63 in 
<taxonomicName id="59CF17A07B87D4A4DEE3E31C5C665028" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus minutus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutus">Madascincus minutus</taxonomicName>
, 56-61 in 
<taxonomicName id="D78AD6735BC0E9C6B8419EDEE0355416" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus melanopleura" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopleura">Madascincus melanopleura</taxonomicName>
, 52-60 in 
<taxonomicName id="2801D4FEE7C326638C541253805036E1" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus nanus" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">Madascincus nanus</taxonomicName>
complex, 59-63 in 
<taxonomicName id="4749B35CF15C778638960D4557D13E89" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus ankodabensis" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ankodabensis">Madascincus ankodabensis</taxonomicName>
, 65-73 in 
<taxonomicName id="E70368305285064148E9741849DAE744" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus miafina" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="miafina">Madascincus miafina</taxonomicName>
, 63-66 in 
<taxonomicName id="56874C11D40E47E8ED2472C6AD754628" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Madascincus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Madascincus mouroundavae" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mouroundavae">Madascincus mouroundavae</taxonomicName>
